main event: Multiple UFO sightings and encounters were documented in Cheyenne, Wyoming on August 7, 1956, including observations by USAF personnel and a patrolman from the Cheyenne Police Department.
interesting points: Sergeant Miller and Airman First Class Wilcox, both stationed at F.E. Warren Air Force Base, observed a small disc-shaped object hovering near the base, moving at high speeds, and disappearing in a matter of seconds.
A civilian reported a round, luminous, and bright object passing over a car, leaving traces on the windshield and causing damage.

The Cheyenne Police Department received a report from a patrolman who observed a cigar-shaped object in the sky, estimated to be 50 to 60 feet in length, which suddenly accelerated and disappeared after being observed for 10-15 minutes.
Photographs and statements from credible witnesses, including USAF personnel and a police patrolman, were included in the report.
The report concluded that based on the limited information provided, no definitive conclusions could be drawn regarding the nature or origin of the unidentified flying objects.
witnesses: USAF personnel, civilian, patrolman from Cheyenne Police Department
